node.text:
Checked yourself lately? It’s important to us that we empower womankind to feel confident in their own skin so this International Women’s Day we’re happy to show our support for @pinkhopeaus - a breast and ovarian preventative health hub with the vision to empower each family to take control of their breast and ovarian cancer risk and to not do it alone.

One of the amazing things they do is bring awareness to a gene fault called BRCA1 and other genetic connections that predisposes the carrier to a risk of breast and ovarian cancer and supports carriers with potentially life-saving information.

You get to be a part of this campaign and look good doing it! For every purchase from our exclusive MESHKI Denim collection, we’re donating $30 to Pink Hope to celebrate International Women’s Day.

So we’re calling you to: Check Yourself, Check Your Breasts and to Check Your Genes with us here at MESHKI & with Pink Hope. Exclusive to www.meshki.com.au

Today we launch the Future is Female Project, to spread awareness of causes close to our hearts and empower women and girls around the world. Which is why we’ve joined forces with @dressforsuccess - a global not-for-profit organisation that empowers women to achieve economic independence by providing a network of support, professional attire, and the development tools to help women thrive in work and in life. 

We're donating $20 of every $100 you spend on the #MESHKIFutureisFemale Collection to @dressforsuccess between 22 and 31 July. 

“Our changing rooms are changing lives.” 🙌🏽

Shop to donate now from our restocked #MESHKIFutureisFemale collection at www.meshki.com.au
The type of nudes we’d like to send you 😉 Which neutral is your fave? 1, 2 or 3? ✨ Tell us & we might just treat you! Exclusive to www.meshki.com.au
